items.title: Indians choosing slow travel, 85 percent willing to spend up to 50 percent more, shows Thomas Cook's holiday report
items.description: More Indians, close to 75 percent are choosing experiential travel, or bucket list items like Northern Lights in Norway, or Japan cherry blossoms. The survey also saw an uptick in safaris, self-drives, and outdoor adventures.

items.title: Solar module maker Emmvee eyes Rs 2,500–3,000 crore via IPO, joins the fundraise bandwagon
items.description: The Emmvee Group has a total manufacturing capacity of 2.5 gigawatts (GW) and 6.6 GW for solar cells and solar modules.

items.title: Electricity prices crash to zero on exchanges as cooler weather cuts May power demand
items.description: With the monsoon arriving sooner, the Ministry of Power plans to reassess its peak power demand projections for this year, which are currently pegged at 270 GW.

items.title: India Inc to benefit from Aatmanirbharta goal in stealth aircraft procurement
items.description: The AMCA is designed to fill a gap in India's air force, which currently lacks a fifth-generation stealth fighter. The opening up of the field for private companies should lend impetus to the programme and to indigenous capabilities
